OL,3,CLib Dems lose majority control of Hull
OL,4,Cas Reform wins 10 seats
OL,6,FOfficials at the council say a turnout
OL,7,Fof 30.25% for Hull is "high for us."
OL,8,FBut with fewer than a third of people
OL,9,Fengaging, others might argue it
OL,10,Fdemonstrates dismay.
OL,12,FFor comparison, in the last general
OL,13,Felection in 2024, the Hull East
OL,14,Fconstituency recorded the UK's third
OL,15,Flowest turnout figure at 42.2%.
OL,17,FThose that did head to the polls were
OL,18,Fvoting on big issues including
OL,19,Fpotholes, schools, playgrounds and the
OL,20,Fcollection of bins.
OL,26,@oD@WOUoD@dO]
